alfredsnippet.name: Compares two objects to determine if the first one contains equivalent property values to the second one, based on a provided function.
alfredsnippet.snippet:
const matchesWith = (obj, source, fn) =>
  Object.keys(source).every(
    key =>
      obj.hasOwnProperty(key) && fn
        ? fn(obj[key], source[key], key, obj, source)
        : obj[key] == source[key]
  );
